snippet.textDisplay: I absolutely HATE pinhole cameras!  I like the front facing bezel where you can have speakers and a camera that doesn't have anything else on it.  There's no point in 18:9 aspect ratios since any aspect ratio on a phone that is not 16:9 is pointless since all videos are 16:9.  This edge to edge display is also not what I want.  It does not look better, it looks worse because of the compromises you must make in order to fit speakers and a camera in front.  So glad I ordered a pixel 3a while it was on sale from dec 26-31/2019 for $399 CND.

*R7-4800U*
Ya, but is it based on Zen 2 or Zen 3 architecture? It really pisses me off when APU's based on previous architectures are named in a misleading fashion. For all we know it's basically an R9-3900x topology (2xCCD chips + IO chip) with one of the 8-core CCD's swapped out for a GPU sharing DDR4 system memory.
